                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18421128-name-1282" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18421128-name-1282" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18421128-name-1282" type="surname" value="DANIELS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18421128-name-1282" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM DANIELS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a publican, and live at Woolwich. On the 4th of Nov. I was outside my door, and saw the prisoner come out of my house, and this pewter measure drop from his person, about ten yards from my door—if he had been drinking he would have used it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. CLARKSON</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> You told the Magistrate you did not believe he had any intention of stealing it? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes, and the Magistrate ordered him to be discharged on bail—he said that he stooped down outside</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184211280167"></xptr>
               <p>the door, saw the measure, and picked it up; but having been drinking, he dropped it again; but he did not do so.</p>
